<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC4FFD2FF29FE53BB95CEFA" pageId="23" pageNumber="244" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC4FFD2FF29FE53BB95CEFA" blockId="23.[136,1452,446,1157]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FF29FE53BE30CEDE" bold="true" box="[136,261,446,472]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—This species is characterized by having morphologically similar telial stage to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC4FFD2FB31FE52BA4CCEDE" box="[1168,1401,446,472]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="23" pageNumber="244" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-pediformis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FB31FE52BA4CCEDE" box="[1168,1401,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">P. caricis-pediformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but shape and size of teliospores are different and the species are also phylogenetically separated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
