<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC4FFD2FF1CFDA3BB27CD6E" box="[189,1042,590,617]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC4FFD2FF1CFDA3BB27CD6E" blockId="23.[136,1452,446,1157]" box="[189,1042,590,617]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FF1CFDA3BE51CD6E" bold="true" box="[189,356,590,616]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Etymology:—</emphasis>
Named after host plant genus and slender-shaped teliospores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC4FFD2FF1CFD9FBA2ECDFE" pageId="23" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC4FFD2FF1CFD9FBA2ECDFE" blockId="23.[136,1452,446,1157]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FF1CFD9FBE64CD8A" bold="true" box="[189,337,626,652]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FECCFD9EBD37CD8B" box="[365,514,627,653]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Spermogonia</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FDB4FD9EBD67CD8A" box="[533,594,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">aecia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FD33FD9FBDC5CD8A" box="[658,752,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">uredinia</emphasis>
not found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FCDEFD9FBC83CD8A" box="[895,950,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Telia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, compact, black, rounded to broadly elliptic, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FE1FFD7BBD08CDB6" box="[446,573,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, mostly truncate at apices, constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 44.5–62.0 × 12.0–16.0 µm (av. 50.5 × 14.5 µm); walls brown, 0.5–1.1 µm (av. 0.8 µm) thick at sides, 9.8–13.7 µm (av. 11.4 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 8.0–18.5 µm (av. 13.0 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
